Versions:
- MediaPipe 0.10.21
- Python 3.10

Packages:
- pandas
- numpy
- lshashpy3

In data_processing, I provided the scripts for getting the MediaPipe data out of citation-form videos (preprocessing_for_LSH.ipynb), and for running Locality-Sensitive Hashing (LSH) to determine the similarity of a test sign.
I also provided a test sign (chocolate-me.mov), as well as a handful of citation forms from Bill Vickers (asl_citation_forms folder). 
You can use these scripts and the test data to play around with LSH analysis locally; the full analysis will have to be run on the Unicorn cluster.
